# Documented multi-error behavior: when a package has a non-(T,error) child-prop
# tuple AND an unrelated type error (undefined symbol elsewhere), the behavior is:
# - The unrelated type error (undefined symbol) surfaces normally.
# - The tuple-rejection diagnostic may be deferred / absent on the same pass because
#   go/types bails out early when a symbol can't be resolved.
#
# This is the KNOWN TRADEOFF: in a clean package (no other errors), the "only
# (T, error) is supported" diagnostic fires. In a broken package, go/types' error
# recovery may suppress it. This case pins the current documented behavior so any
# future change is an explicit decision.
-- input.gsx --
package views

func twoInts() (int, int) { return 1, 2 }

component Card(x int) { <div>{x}</div> }

component Page() {
	<Card x={twoInts()}/>
	<div>{undefinedSym}</div>
}
-- diagnostics.golden --
9:8: undefined: undefinedSym
